<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301985">Figure 85</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301985" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301985" filename="../figg13/G1301985.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 85. Gear Shift Lever Assembly Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove boot from gear shift lever and secure assembly in vise with bottom of housing up.
                    Use a large screwdriver to twist between spring and housing, forcing spring from under lugs in the
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301986">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
                    <emph type="bold">Do one coil at a time.</emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301986" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301986" filename="../figg13/G1301986.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 86. Force Spring From Under Lugs</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer and gear shift lever from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301987">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301987" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301987" filename="../figg13/G1301987.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 87. Remove Tension Spring, Washer and Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spade pin from the bore in the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301988">Figure 88</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the O-ring from the groove
                    inside the tower.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301988" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301988" filename="../figg13/G1301988.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 88. Remove Spade Pin From Housing Tower Bore</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
